4. Time-Series Graph (Star Rating Change over time)


1) Change by Date



star_date <- select(points1, score, time)
tmp <- strptime(star_date$time, "%Y.%m.%d %H")
tmp <- paste0(tmp$mon+1, " ", tmp$mday, "")
star_date$time <- tmp
star_date <- filter(star_date, "7 2" == str_sub(star_date$time, 1, 5) |
                               "7 3" == str_sub(star_date$time, 1, 5) |
                               "7 4" == str_sub(star_date$time, 1, 5))
star_date$score <- factor(star_date$score, levels=c(10:1))



() 


star_date_bar <- star_date %>%
  group_by(time, score) %>%
  summarise(score_freq = n()) %>%
  arrange(time, score)
star_date_bar
## # A tibble: 30 x 3

##  8 7 2 3              4
##  9 7 2 2             43
## 10 7 2 1             59
## # ... with 20 more rows
star_date_bar2 <- star_date_bar %>%  
  mutate(pct = score_freq/sum(score_freq)*100) %>%
  mutate(ylabel_b = str_c(score, " (", format(pct, digits=2), "%)")) %>%
  arrange(desc(score)) %>%
  mutate(ypos = cumsum(score_freq) - 0.5*score_freq) %>%
  arrange(time, desc(score))

ggplot(data=star_date_bar2, aes(x=time, y=score_freq, fill=score)) +

star_date2 <- select(points1, score, time)
tmp <- strptime(star_date2$time, "%Y.%m.%d %H:%M")

time_tmp <- rep(NA, length(tmp))
for(i in 1:length(tmp)) {
  ifelse(tmp$hour[i] <= 4, time_tmp[i] <- paste0(tmp[i]$mon+1, " ", tmp[i]$mday, " ", "1~4"),
  ifelse(tmp$hour[i] <= 8, time_tmp[i] <- paste0(tmp[i]$mon+1, " ", tmp[i]$mday, " ", "4~8"),
  ifelse(tmp$hour[i] <= 12, time_tmp[i] <- paste0(tmp[i]$mon+1, " ", tmp[i]$mday, " ", "8~12"),
  ifelse(tmp$hour[i] <= 16, time_tmp[i] <- paste0(tmp[i]$mon+1, " ", tmp[i]$mday, " ", "12~16"),
  ifelse(tmp$hour[i] <= 20, time_tmp[i] <- paste0(tmp[i]$mon+1, " ", tmp[i]$mday, " ", "16~20"),
  time_tmp[i] <- paste0(tmp$mon[i]+1, " ", tmp$mday[i], " ", "21~24"))))))
}

star_date2$time <- time_tmp
star_date2 <- filter(star_date2, "7 2" == str_sub(star_date2$time, 1, 5) |
                                 "7 3" == str_sub(star_date2$time, 1, 5) |
                                 "7 4" == str_sub(star_date2$time, 1, 5))
star_date2$score <- as.character(star_date2$score)
star_date2$score <- as.numeric(star_date2$score)

star_hour_line2 <- star_date2 %>%
  group_by(time) %>%
  summarise(avg_score = mean(score))
